%N A392988 Numbers k such that there is a primitive Pythagorean triple with perimeter k and inradius r such that p + r, p - r, p + r^2 and |p - r^2| are all prime.
%C A392988 The first term that corresponds to more than one value of the inradius is a(344) = 1915880, where the primitive Pythagorean triples (491208, 627655, 797017) and (627655, 491208, 797017) have perimeter 1915880 and inradii 160923 and 111867 respectively.
%H A392988 Robert Israel, <a href="/A392988/b392988.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A392988 a(3) = 132 is a term because the primitive Pythagorean triple (11, 60, 61) has perimeter 132 and inradius 5, and 132 + 5 = 137, 132 - 5 = 127, 132 + 5^2 = 157 and 132 - 5^2 = 107 are all prime.
%p A392988 N:= 60000: # for terms <= N
%p A392988 S:= {}:
%p A392988 for x from 2 by 2 while 2*x^2<N do
%p A392988   for y from 1 by 2 to min(x-1, (N-2*x^2)/(2*x)) do
%p A392988        if igcd(x, y) > 1 then next fi;
%p A392988        p:= 2*x^2 + 2*x*y;
%p A392988        r:= x*y - y^2;
%p A392988        if andmap(isprime,[p+r^2,abs(p-r^2),p+r,abs(p-r)]) then S:= S union {p} fi
%p A392988 od od:
%p A392988 sort(convert(S,list));
